cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a framework for learning stabilizable nonlinear dynamical systems for continuous control tasks in robotics. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The paper also leverages tools from statistical learning and convex optimization, which suggests that it could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses concepts from nonlinear control theory, which suggests that it could belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. The paper also involves reinforcement learning, which suggests that it could belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a novel algorithm for learning stabilizable dynamics, which suggests that it could also belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
